I usually try to avoid Starbucks but I was desperate for coffee. This is a beautiful Starbucks, plenty of places to sit, very clean and modern. But the service is quite disorganized. The staff are friendly but they seemed to care more about their conversation then taking care of customers. I don't mind casual working environment, but they were too casual. There is also no clearly marked line for the registers, so you have people deciding what to order and people just coming in and heading straight to the register. I thought I was in line but people kept ordering in front of me. The cappuccino was ok, nothing special, tasted bit burnt.

Sitting in this Starbucks and watching all of the locals come through is a fantastic experience, as you will see one big smile after another as they interact with the employees here. Starbucks as a corporation should use this location as an example for what do at their other locations! Come here and you won't be disappointed!
